<item>
            <title>[FLINK-27479] HybridSource refreshes availability future</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-27479</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HybridSourceReader needs to refresh the availability future according to the underlying reader. It currently maintains its own future and completes it after the sub-reader&apos;s availability future is complete. However, the implementation does not refresh the future again until the reader receives a switch event. This can cause a tight loop with the Flink runtime repeatedly invoking pollNext() and high CPU utilization.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To solve this, we can reuse the MultipleFuturesAvailabilityHelper to manage the lifecycle of the availability future.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
